    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-03-07T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-03-07T08:00:00-05:00" n="413"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d413">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">684A.86/3–752: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 413<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Israel (<persName corresp="#p_DMB1"
                            type="from">Davis</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d413fn1">Repeated to London, Paris, Ankara, Amman, Baghdad,
                        Cairo, Damascus, Jerusalem, Beirut, and Karachi.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tel Aviv</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-03-07T15:00:00+02:00"
                            >March 7, 1952—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>922. Re <gloss target="#t_Depcirtel1">Depcirtel</gloss> 758, Mar. 4. Emb believes
                    still too early judge real significance and effect “peace feelers” and whether
                    they may lead to improvement Arab-Israel relations. Official and public comment
                    here has been cautious with strong undertone suspicion of Arab motives. Suspect
                    attempt achieve acceptance Arab League Collective Security Org as chosen
                    instrument <gloss target="#t_ME1">ME</gloss> defense (<gloss target="#t_Embtel1"
                        >Embtel</gloss> 881, Feb 27,<note n="2" xml:id="d413fn2">In telegram 891,
                        Feb. 29, the Embassy referred to apprehension on the part of the Israeli
                        press that the inclusion of the Arab states in a regional military structure
                        would be to the ultimate disadvantage of Israel. (684A.86/2–2952)</note> 891
                    and 897, Feb 29, 905, Mar 3<note n="3" xml:id="d413fn3">In telegram 905, Mar. 3,
                        the Embassy reported in part that although there was a genuine interest in
                        “peace feelers” from Arab sources, official and public reaction in Israel
                        was one of caution or suspicion. (684A.86/3–352)</note>).</p>
                <p>Emb concurs in views probable significance of developments in question not great.
                    Considers them noteworthy only because even slight change in generally negative
                    attitude is hopeful.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DMB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
